				\begin{document}$$X = \left( {m_{0} - m} \right)/\left( {m_{0} - m_{{\text{a}}} } \right) \times {1}00\%$$\end{document}where RX determines the reactivity at the X th degree of carbon conversion, 1/s; m0 is initial char weight, g; ma is ash weight, g; m is instant char weight at time t, g; dm/dt—weight loss of the char at X th degree of carbon conversion. The tests determined the reactivity at 50% carbon conversion (R50) and the maximum reactivity (Rmax).

